text: Otaki in Iburi Subprefecture was a village located in Usu District, Iburi Subprefecture, Hokkaido, Japan. As of 2004, the village had an estimated population of 2,054 and a density of 7.50 persons per km². The total area was 274.03 km². On 1 March 2006, Ōtaki was merged into the city of Date. ==External links== * Date official website Category:Dissolved municipalities of Hokkaido
